{
    "suite": "creator-core-scenarios",
    "_comment": "Realistic cross-lane scenario contract, run by tools/scenario_check.py. TEST-ONLY: it exercises what exists today and pins what does not (the gap_ledger). Findings-as-contract: the runner fails if a leg breaks, if a declared-absent classification appears in the hub routing table, OR if a gap probe stops observing its gap; either direction forces this file and docs/SCENARIOS.md to be updated deliberately. All fixture data is fictional.",
    "schema_version": "0.1.0",
    "pinned_today": "2026-09-15",
    "defaults": {
        "lead_days": 3
    },
    "gap_ledger": [],
    "_closed_gaps": {
        "G7": "Closed by P32: the mediakit-critique atom and the partnership-mediakit content_critique action critique the creator's own media kit against the market (benchmark-compare per metric plus a structural review), honestly degrading to structural_only when the benchmark rows are unsourced (null). quality-review stays the internal-Quality-Gates lens; the two do not overlap.",
        "G3": "Closed by P32: the hub routing table gained account_read (account-manager, read-only account and contact lookup) and deal_status (deal-pipeline, read-only lifecycle status). S1 keeps crm_query and contact_lookup pinned absent deliberately: account_read subsumes them and contact_lookup is a spoke action, not a hub route (anti-synonym-bloat).",
        "G1": "Closed by P32: the contact-lookup atom and the account-manager contact_lookup action resolve a brand phrase (account-resolve) then read the contact rows via tools/accounts.contacts(); the contact_lookup MCP tool exposes the same read. A person hint that matches nobody returns a gap naming the known contacts, never the wrong person; contact PII is masked when it leaves the machine.",
        "G2": "Closed by P32: tools/accounts.py resolve() does tiered brand-phrase matching (exact, alias, substring, difflib fuzzy, brand-category term map) over an aliases[] field now in account-schema.json; the account-resolve atom wraps it and account-health delegates fuzzy resolution to it. Never auto-picks past a confident exact or alias match.",
        "G4": "Closed by P32: account-schema.json v0.2.0 reconciled to shared/pipeline-engine.md (brand_category enum including lighting, secondary_contacts, relationship_health, channel_preferences, deal_history_summary, renewal_candidate); product_category kept deprecated for pre-v0.2.0 records.",
        "G5": "Closed by P32: canonical-sources/seasonal-aesthetic.md now exists (aesthetic profiles plus the reconciled eight-window timing table); drift invariant 22 (frontmatter load refs) and canonical-sources in KNOWN_ROOTS close the scan hole that let the dangling ref escape.",
        "G6": "Closed by P32: canonical-sources/seasonal-aesthetic/seasonal.json gained the seasonal-windows entry with resolved ISO dates for reference_year 2026 (annual recurrence stated); the engine table, seasonal-map table, and JSON are reconciled to the same eight windows.",
        "G8": "Closed by P30: benchmarks.json rate rows gained structured low/high/unit/currency (parsed from their own prose) and benchmark-compare's 6 metric rows now exist with the low/high/unit schema, values sourced-or-null (null until verified against a registered rate-benchmark source; never estimated).",
        "G9": "Closed by P28: shared/docintel/transcripts.py gap_metrics() and suggest_chapters() provide pause/silence and words_per_minute analysis from transcript timecodes.",
        "G10": "Closed by P28: footage_breakdown classification routes to video-development (footage-analysis atom)."
    },
    "scenarios": [
        {
            "id": "S1-contact-lookup",
            "utterance": "what's the email for that guy from my Hearthline account?",
            "routing": {
                "mode": "present",
                "present": [
                    {
                        "classification": "account_read",
                        "spoke": "account-manager"
                    }
                ],
                "absent_classifications": [
                    "crm_query",
                    "contact_lookup"
                ],
                "note": "account_read (account-manager) resolves 'that guy' via account-resolve then contact-lookup. crm_query and contact_lookup stay pinned absent on purpose: account_read subsumes the read intent and contact_lookup is a spoke action, not a hub route."
            },
            "legs": [
                {
                    "id": "account-record-shape",
                    "op": "json.load",
                    "with": {
                        "fixture": "hearthline-account.json"
                    },
                    "assert": [
                        {
                            "path": "primary_contact.email",
                            "check": "not_null"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "primary_contact.name",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "Marcus Webb"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "secondary_contacts",
                            "check": "len_gte",
                            "value": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "secondary_contacts[0].email",
                            "check": "not_null"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "relationship_health",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "warm"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "aliases",
                            "check": "len_gte",
                            "value": 1
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "hearthline-resolve",
                    "op": "accounts.resolve",
                    "with": {
                        "fixture": "accounts-roster.json",
                        "query": "hearthline"
                    },
                    "assert": [
                        {
                            "path": "resolved.account_id",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "acct-hearthline-001"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "computed_by",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "tools/accounts.py.resolve"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "hearth-ambiguous",
                    "op": "accounts.resolve",
                    "with": {
                        "fixture": "accounts-roster.json",
                        "query": "hearth"
                    },
                    "assert": [
                        {
                            "path": "resolved",
                            "check": "null"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "candidates",
                            "check": "len_eq",
                            "value": 2
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "that-guy-contact",
                    "op": "accounts.contacts",
                    "with": {
                        "fixture": "accounts-roster.json",
                        "query": "hearthline",
                        "person": "marcus"
                    },
                    "assert": [
                        {
                            "path": "contacts",
                            "check": "len_eq",
                            "value": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "contacts[0].name",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "Marcus Webb"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "contacts[0].email",
                            "check": "not_null"
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "computed_by",
                            "check": "eq",
                            "value": "tools/accounts.py.contacts"
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "unknown-person-refused",
                    "op": "accounts.contacts",
                    "with": {
                        "fixture": "accounts-roster.json",
                        "query": "hearthline",
                        "person": "nobody by this name"
                    },
                    "assert": [
                        {
                            "path": "contacts",
                            "check": "len_eq",
                            "value": 0
                        },
                        {
                            "path": "gaps",
                            "check": "len_gte",
                            "value": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "known_gaps": []
        },
